The paper discusses the comparison of several algorithms for symbolic regression, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also compares the performance of these algorithms with conventional machine learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of synthetic and real-world benchmark problems, which could fall under cs.DM (Data Mining) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
